WP: Quartz.NET job scheduler — TCP probe implementation
Feature: 004-network-test-execution
Estimate: 2h
Dependencies: WP01 (003-network-test-config)

Tasks:
1. Implement NetworkTestJob (IJob) — TCP connect probe with timeout
2. Implement INetworkProbeFactory returning correct INetworkProbe per ServiceType
3. Implement TcpPortProbe (most common service type, used as base for all TCP-based types)
4. Implement HttpEndpointProbe (uses HttpClient, checks response < 599)
5. Implement DnsResolveProbe
6. Register all jobs from the NetworkTestDefinitions table on API startup
7. On new test create/update/delete, refresh Quartz scheduler

Acceptance:
- AC-004-01: TcpPort probe succeeds/fails correctly against a known open/closed port
- AC-004-02: HttpEndpoint probe records latency in ms
- AC-004-03: Failed probe stores ErrorMessage in NetworkTestResult
- AC-004-04: Quartz job runs at the configured cron schedule
- AC-004-05: Disabled tests do not trigger probes
